metatags.og:description: Celestine "Tina" Beyincé-Lawson[4][6] (born January 4, 1954) is an American businesswoman and fashion designer known for her House of Deréon and Miss Tina by Tina Knowles fashion brands. She is the mother of singers Beyoncé and Solange Knowles, and is the ex-wife of Mathew Knowles, the manager of Destiny's Child as well as Beyoncé and Kelly Rowland until 2011.Personal lifeKnowles was born Célestine Ann Beyincé in Galveston, Texas, on January 4, 1954, the daughter of Lumis Albert Beyincé and Agnes Derouen.[4] Her ancestry is Creole (African, Native American, and French). Her family roots are from Iberia Parish, Louisiana.[6][7] She is a descendant of Acadian leader Joseph Broussard.[8] She married Mathew Knowles on January 5, 1980 in Galveston, Texas.
